"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-nbc-huge-ratings-early-days-paris-olympic\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"1.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 2, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m not an Olympics person.\", \"from\": 3, \"to\": 32, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just not my thing.\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 58, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t watch and don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t follow what\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s going on.\", \"from\": 59, \"to\": 115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But from the very little I was on Twitter over the weekend, I know there was some big controversy about the opening ceremony and people were going on and on about boycotting the Games.\", \"from\": 116, \"to\": 300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 150, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6124607852278486e-29, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s how the boycott has worked out.\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony on Friday drew 28.6 million viewers, the best viewership number for the opening ceremony since 2012.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Saturday, NBC drew 32.4 million viewers for the Olympics, up 83% from the same day of the Tokyo Games in 2020.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 479, \"end\": 482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999487650576784, \"rank\": 5.123562580110966e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Sunday, NBC drew 41.5 million for the Olympics, up nearly 50% from the same day of the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999487650576784, \"rank\": 5.123562580110966e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympics are up 79% from the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC platforms averaged 34.5 million viewers over the first three days.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999487650576784, \"rank\": 5.123562580110966e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tokyo Games averaged 19.3 million over the first three days.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s U.S. basketball game on Sunday drew 10.9 million viewers.\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was more viewers than the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball gold medal game in the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have asked for a better start in Paris.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1100, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999487650576784, \"rank\": 5.123562580110966e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5593688311411902e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2.Full disclosure: I am not familiar with Rennae Stubbs\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s work as a tennis commentator, so I have no opinion on whether I think she is good or not.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Chris \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMad Dog\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Russo, who is as big a tennis fan as there is, ripped Stubbs for her work during Monday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Rafael Nadal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093Novak Djokovic match at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\", \"score\": 0.5776049158566061, \"rank\": 0.7310046366132131, \"text\": \"Stubbs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\"}, {\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stubbs got wind of Russo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s harsh critique of her work and claimed his take was sexist.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even worse, Stubbs said on Twitter, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cDoes he comment on all the men that talk non stop on broadcasts.\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1528, \"end\": 1534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\", \"score\": 0.5776049158566061, \"rank\": 0.7310046366132131, \"text\": \"Stubbs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\"}, {\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6124607852278486e-29, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Probably not.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  As someone who listens to Russo every single day, I cannot tell you how bad and embarrassing a take this is from Stubbs.\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\", \"score\": 0.5776049158566061, \"rank\": 0.7310046366132131, \"text\": \"Stubbs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rennae_Stubbs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the broadcasters Russo criticizes on a regular basis: Tony Romo, Kevin Harlan and Gus Johnson.\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Harlan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kevin Harlan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Harlan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Harlan\"}, {\"begin\": 1848, \"end\": 1859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gus_Johnson_(sportscaster)\", \"score\": 0.5391337049868883, \"rank\": 0.4392764857880412, \"text\": \"Gus Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gus_Johnson_(sportscaster)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gus_Johnson_(sportscaster)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nobody is more of an equal-opportunity basher when it comes to broadcasters than Chris Russo.\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1942, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Russo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Russo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2722764\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13590141\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Russo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Russo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is called sexism at its best.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 1990, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Does he comment on all the men that talk non stop on broadcasts.\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Probably not.\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"3.When one bettor lost out on a four-leg home run parlay Sunday because Brent Rooker didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t go deep, he let the A\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s outfielder know about it.\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The gambler probably didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t expect Rooker to respond, but he did and it was fantastic.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brent Rooker had the time yesterday \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0082(via@Skunkii_Plays|@FDSportsbook)pic.twitter.com/Gm5jG1Ir4i  4.Did Diamondbacks broadcaster Steve Berthiaume misread this shirt or did he intentionally ad-lib to avoid any possible controversy?\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2440, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Berthiaume\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Berthiaume\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Berthiaume\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Berthiaume\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Either way, he probably wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t thrilled the camera person stayed on the fan that long.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Did Steve Berthiaume accidentally think the kids shirt say \\\"I Can not I am A Moron\\\" rather than \\\"I Can not I am Mormon\\\" \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0082\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0082pic.twitter.com/fygelavJf8  5.Orioles catcher James McCann took a pitch to the face on Monday, which resulted in a bloody and ugly scene.\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2636, \"end\": 2652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Berthiaume\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Berthiaume\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Berthiaume\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Berthiaume\"}, {\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mormons\", \"score\": 0.9713071664574476, \"rank\": 0.02815214243580104, \"text\": \"Mormon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mormons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mormons\"}, {\"begin\": 2806, \"end\": 2818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_McCann_(baseball)\", \"score\": 0.9770798432371438, \"rank\": 0.01042118975249921, \"text\": \"James McCann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_McCann_(baseball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_McCann_(baseball)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James McCann is a legend for this.pic.twitter.com/C6FBFVqF9a  Somehow, McCann STAYED IN THE GAME.\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2899, \"end\": 2911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_McCann_(baseball)\", \"score\": 0.9770798432371438, \"rank\": 0.01042118975249921, \"text\": \"James McCann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_McCann_(baseball)\", \"d